<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-23T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-23T11:00:00-05:00" n="444" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d444">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.00/2943: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Munro</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-23T11:00:00-05:00">April 23, 1931—11
                                a.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>25. Your 18, March 14, 11 a.m. Department has no objection to proposed
                            paragraph regarding commissioning of customs employees.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
